        "id": 5140
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-08-07T20:08:58Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Except span doesn\u0027t own any storage (it\u0027s just a pointer of some type and a length). The storage of initializer_list is hard to reason about, but I\u0027m pretty sure it\u0027s more or less temporary? Like, the user would have to keep the initial initializer_list alive somehow, which is a somewhat odd thing to do. In a range based for loop it\u0027s the `auto \u0026\u0026 __range \u003d range_expression ;` outside the for loop which is keeping the initializer list alive (it\u0027s doing lifetime extension).",
      "parentUuid": "fab3789f_807225fc",
      "revId": "e6532a20c2a1c6033cdc110088883d0d538ce26e",
